rComments: I would not graduate without taking one of his classes. If you're in the social sciences he is a MUST TAKE. His classes are super engaging and really interesting, but you'll get the most out of it if you do the readings (even a skim is sufficient). His grading is average, maybe even on the easier side. He's an amazing prof and I highly recommend

I liked this professor. He knows what he is talking about and keeps the classes interesting. BUT throughout the semester he wanted us to completely read 5 books. These included Leviathan, Second Treatise of Government, Machiavelli's discourses, etc. PLUS other readings weekly. He was also a very harsh grader. You needed to know everything.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Prof Williams is one of the best teachers I've had at UofO. He's a super nice guy and responds quickly to emails!! He is clear with what he wants from his students. He taught material that I had previously learned in other classes soooo much better. He really goes into detail and gives great explanations. LOVE THIS GUY!
Amazing lecturer! Made all content covered interesting.

Prof. Williams is an outstanding lecturer and academic. I had both the honour of having him as my MRP supervisor and as a professor for his Radical Conservatism course. He is a fair marker and provides great written feedback on assignments. Prof. Williams wants to see his students succeed, and always makes himself available to answer any questions.

Amazing professor, definitely the best class I've ever taken. He was the first professor to ever give me actual criticism on my writing abilities, and I feel that I will be able to use the skills I learned from this class in order to do better in the future. Expects a lot in the take-home exams, my lowest grade from the semester but worth it!

Hes a really good prof. he is very engaging and his classes are very interesting Theres plenty of long and boring readings to do. he doesnt use powerpoints so coming in class is very is a must. His exam are difficult but you can definitely get a good great if you work for it.

Professor Williams is one of the best lecturers I've ever had. He is VERY engaging and makes you want to attend his lectures. He does not use powerpoint. He assigns long and boring readings. His exams are difficult and he asks for a lot on them but they aren't terrible.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: One of the best profs I have ever had. Lectures are so compelling and interesting. Highly recommend.

He is a really good prof! It was a pleasure going to his class.  I am a french student and he was really clear and he takes your attention good lecture etc. If you have a chance to take him please do!

Professor Williams is an absolute riot. He's hilarious and conveys political philosophy is a way I never imagined possible. His readings are the longest I've had for any class but he ties everything together very well in his lectures. Doesn't use blackboard or PowerPoint and yet still manages to lecture better than any other prof I've ever had.

Single handedly the most inspirational, passionate professor I have ever had in university. Attending his lectures became something that I looked forward to doing every week. His ability to capture the attention of his students and convey the material in an interesting way is extremely unique. He deserves every bit of praise that he has received.

Absolutely the best prof I've ever had. All his lectures felt like watching a movie, the time just flies by. He is eloquent, clear, and absolutely riveting. There were no papers for this class, but TONS of readings. I promise you, though, this class is entirely worth the work. I might take it again anyways, it's THAT GOOD.
He is right up there with Francisco Gonzalez as the best Profs at the University.  Just a straight G.

Fantastic prof who is one of the best lecturers Ive ever had. Engages the class and makes philosophy relevant and interesting. Exams are relatively straight forward but make sure you have studied the philosophers in many areas as the questions tend to be specific. Take this course whether you love philosophy or not! He's a legend

Literally one of the best courses I have ever taken! He is such an amazing prof and his excitement and enthusiasm for his material is remarkable! You have to attend class to do well, but he doesn't make attending his lectures awful! You will want to be in class each time! Great professor, honestly!

Only time I've ever bothered writing a review for a Prof. Took the course expecting it to be boring as hell, he made this course a blast. Does a fantastic job explaining the course material, very funny and engaging lectures. Readings aren't mandatory, but attending the lectures if you want a great mark is recommended. 10/10, would take again.
Fantastic!! He verbalizes course material in a very story-like manner which always kept me engaged. One of the most approachable profs outside of class!!
By far the best Prof!!! His lectures are very well structured and it helps to understand the readings. He really does have a passion for teaching, he wants to see his students succeed.

This professor is hands down the best professor I have ever had! I took this class because I felt politically ignorant and his lectures made me feel edumacated. I used brain muscles in this class I didn't know I had. Totally obsessed with this prof. His tone and manner of lecturing are so clear and easy to understand. He's also so mysterious.
Conprenssion is never a problem, he always knows how to make you understand anything and everything he's talking about. Great man

Amazing! Such a great speaker. I've been taught about Hobbes, Locke and Rousseau in countless other classes, but this class made their ideas and contributions to political/philosophical thought crystal clear. Go to class, take notes and enjoy.
Best professor I have had hands down. No surprises on exams and crystal clear in class. Attendance is mandatory, however, and if you want to get over a B you must read the material.
He is amazing. As long as you attend class you will do well. No powerpoints, just debates and philosophical issues about politics. Best class i have ever taken

This guy is amazing. You go to his class, you sit, you listen, and you learn. He has this amazing tone to his voice that makes the material so interesting, even though it I thought reading it was boring. He's fairly easy, I'd say attendance is mandatory. But man, this guy is awesome.

Easily the best professor I have ever had. He was passionate and engaging. Walked in, no notes,no microphone, no powerpoint and just talked to us. He made class fun and was very helpful in office hours. Tests are difficult but manageable if you come to lecture and study. Wish I could have him for every class! I can never get enough of this man!
